&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Own the end-to-end accounts payable process across all directly-managed entities: vendor onboarding, invoice processing, payment runs, expense reports, and vendor relationship management.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Lead the general accounting operations: journal entries, bank reconciliations, fixed assets, accruals, prepayments, and intercompany bookings — ensuring accurate, timely month-end and year-end closes.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Manage and develop a team of three (AP Accountant, General Accountant, Intern): set priorities, coach, review work and build technical depth within the team.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Partner with the Accounting &amp;amp; Tax Director on the design and implementation of accounting policies, internal controls and process improvements.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Lead Finance × IT initiatives within scope: AP automation tools, ERP improvements, expense management systems and approval workflows.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Support statutory audits and tax filings by preparing required schedules, reconciliations and supporting documentation across entities.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Act as a true business partner to Operations, Procurement, Retail and HQ teams — building trust, anticipating needs and ensuring smooth vendor management.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
