&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Own lifecycle marketing strategy across email, SMS, and app push — from welcome through repeat purchase, reactivation, and loyalty. You build the programs and run them.&amp;nbsp;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Comfort with AI-native workflows is not a nice-to-have here, it is how we expect this function to operate.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Platform strategy. Evaluate, recommend, and lead the implementation of our CRM and ESP stack, with a clear point of view on what the right architecture looks like for a brand at our stage and pace.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Acquisition-to-retention handoff. Partner with Performance Marketing on audience strategy, suppression logic, and the seam between paid acquisition and owned retention, making sure we do not lose customers we paid to acquire.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Retail clienteling partnership. Work closely with the retail team to translate CRM data and segmentation intelligence into clienteling tactics in store, helping identify the right customers for outreach, the right moments to engage, and the right messages to deliver. The goal is a unified customer experience where the relationship does not reset at the door.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Creative partnership. Brief and collaborate with the Creative team on lifecycle assets across campaigns, evergreen programs, and seasonal moments.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Retention analytics. Build reporting frameworks tied to the metrics that matter, repeat rate, LTV, lapsed rate, and translate what the data says into what we do next.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
